groups except more non-dissection were included in aTAA (74.2%) than non-aTAA 
(48.1%). There were no significant differences in intraoperative variables and 
endotracheal intubation time and ICU staying time were shorter in aTAA (not 
significant). No significant differences were revealed in operative morbidity, 
mortality and five-year actual survival rate between two groups. 16.1% of early 
mortality and 9.7% of hospital mortality for operated aTAA were acceptable, 
which let us conclude that aTAA must be operated positively before rupture by 
careful selection considering life expectancy, evaluation of risk factors or 
reserved physiological status, and surgical invasion.

