The role of profunda femoris revascularization in aortofemoral surgery. An 
analysis of factors affecting graft patency.

Bastounis E(1), Felekouras E, Pikoulis E, Hadjinikolaou L, Georgopoulos S, Balas 
P.

Author information:
(1)First Surgical Department, Medical School, University of Athens Laiko General 
Hospital, Greece.

BACKGROUND: To determine the long-term results of aortofemoral grafts using the 
profunda femoris artery as an outflow vessel and to determine the factors 
affecting the outcome of these procedures.
DESIGN: Prospective study.
METHODS: From 1980 to 1993, 224 profundoplasties were performed as an adjunctive 
outflow procedure of aortofemoral grafts in 180 patients. There were 167 men and 
13 women with a mean age of 63.7 years. Severe claudication was the indication 
